The paper proposes a new method for structured regression in spatio-temporal datasets with missing labels, which is a common problem in many real-life applications. The method is based on probabilistic graphical models and is aimed at learning from both labeled and unlabeled parts of the data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with partially observed attributed graphs, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper includes experiments on predicting precipitation based on climate variables, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
